== Previous Related Tutorials {{<a name="related"></a>}}

Our tutorial is unique in that it aims at providing a broad coverage of image
and surface analysis applications while employing a common theoretical
framework. The relevant topics have been already covered by multiple different
tutorials at ICCV, CVPR, and ECCV over the last three years, but we envisage to
provide a unified view of their relationships.

=== Surface analysis

ECCV 2010, CVPR 2011: [http://tosca.cs.technion.ac.il/book/course_eccv10.html Diffusion Geometry in Shape Analysis] (Michael Bronstein, Alex Bronstein, and Radu Horaud)

ICCV 2013: Spectral geometry methods in 3D data analysis (Alex Bronstein, Michael Bronstein)

=== Feature learning

ECCV 2010: [http://ufldl.stanford.edu/eccv10-tutorial Feature Learning for Image Classification] (Kai Yu and Andrew Ng)

CVPR 2012: [http://www.iro.umontreal.ca/~memisevr/multiview-feature-learning-cvpr Multiview Feature Learning]  (Roland Memisevic)

CVPR 2012: [http://cs.nyu.edu/~fergus/tutorials/deep_learning_cvpr12 Deep Learning Methods for Vision] (Rob Fergus, Honglak Lee, Marc'Aurelio Ranzato, Graham Taylor, Ruslan Salakhutdinov, Kai Yu)

=== Sparse coding

CVPR 2010: [http://lear.inrialpes.fr/people/mairal/tutorial_cvpr2010 Tutorial on Sparse Coding and Dictionary Learning for Image Analysis] (F. Bach, J. Mairal, J. Ponce, G. Sapiro)

ECCV 2012: [http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/~yang/courses/ECCV2012 Sparse and Low-Rank Representation for Computer Vision -- Theory, Algorithms and Applications] (Yi Ma, John Wright, Allen Y. Yang)

